obo:ECO_0006063  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2141  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1/2 GRIP1 acts a KIF5A-binding scaffolding protein for GluR2 in vivo.\n\nFig.3 OE of dom neg KIF5A construct competed with the intrinsic KIF5GRIP1 complex and reduced the amounts of GRIP1 and GluR2 in synapses: \"The GFP-KHCCBD construct competed with the intrinsic KIF5-GRIP1 complex (Fig. 3b), and reduced the amounts of GRIP1 (Fig. 3c) and GluR2 in the synapses (Fig. 3e). Control KIF17 tail expression did not abolish GluR2 in the synapses (Fig. 3f)\". Experimental description: - Dissociated neurons are of rat species: \"Biochemical analysis of dominant negative constructs was from mid-density-cultured rat brain neuron\"\n- Over-expressed protein is of mouse species: \"As would be expected if this complex is functional, both gene targeting and dominant negative experiments of heavy chains of mouse kinesin showed abnormal localization of GRIP1\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2141" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

